{
  "stem": "1216.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We played together, we talked together, but we weren't friends, as such.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Hans was a friend.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was a couple of years younger than I, but more or less from the day we met, we were inseparable.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We both went where the other went.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Whatever it is we did, be that to go for food, or see whether we could steal some fuel or-- or food, or something else, or whether we were just walking around, or whatever, but we were always together.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And since he was younger, he was, let's see, eight to my 10, so he stayed with his mother in the women's room.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we were together even there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we played together, in as far as any of us children really played.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Games were camp games.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In the morning, we had an every morning ritual, which became a game, but was really a necessity, and that was to see who could catch more fleas and bed bugs and kill more.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Since we were infested with them-- I earlier mentioned the wooden beds-- the bed bugs crawl into the wood, and eat their way in, and as a result, even when we were chased out of the barracks, and the barracks were then poison gassed to get rid of the vermin, they simply went deeper into the wood and survived it very nicely.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So we came back to the same vermin, needles to say.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They are easier to catch than fleas because they don't jump.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it takes a certain amount of training, however, because, of course, nobody was used to that, even the poorest of the poor pre-war did not have vermin in their houses like that.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So nobody was used to it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But Hans and I were children.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
